<div class="wrap"> <style> #fullarea{ width=60%; } #main { float:left; width:60%; } #sidebar { float:right; width:37%; } #leftlist { float:left; width:50%; } #rightpic { float:right; width:50%; } .codeforcopy{ font-size:12px; lineheight: 14px; }</style> <?php echo "<h2>" . __( 'Notice Boxes', 'nbox_trdom' ) . "</h2>"; ?> <div id="main"> <h3> How to use Notice Boxes </h3> <p> Using notice boxes in your posts and pages is very easy. All you need to do is to add a shortcode. You can also control various options like the type of the box, the alignment of the text and wether to show a close button or not. For example, the following box can be made by using the shortcode mentioned below it. </p> <p> <div> <img src="<?php echo plugins_url( 'images/ss1.png' , __FILE__ ) ?>" /> </div> <code> [nbox type="notice"] Any Text Here [/nbox] </code> </p> <div> <p> Some other types that you can use instead of <code> type="notice" </code> are <div id="leftlist"> <ul class="ul-disc"> <li> <code> type="info"</code> or <code> type="notice"</code> </li> <li> <code> type="success" </code> </li> <li> <code> type="warning" </code> </li> <li> <code> type="error" </code> </li> </ul> </p> </div> <div id="rightpix"> <a href="<?php echo plugins_url( 'images/ss2.png' , __FILE__ ) ?>"><img src="<?php echo plugins_url( 'images/ss2.png' , __FILE__ ) ?>" height = 151px width=350px /></a> </div></div><div id="fullarea"><h4>Center Align & Close Button</h4> <p> You can also make the text <b> center aligned</b> or <b>add a close button </b> . Just add <code> align="center" </code> &nbsp;to the shortcode to make it center aligned and <code>close="yes"</code> or <code>close="true"</code> to the shortcode to add a close button. You can use any type of noticebox with <code> align="center" </code> and <code> close="yes" </code>. For example, the following code: <br> <code> [nbox type="success" align= "center" close="yes"]A center aligned “success” notice box with a close button.[/nbox] </code> <br> will give the following notice box <br> <img src="<?php echo plugins_url( 'images/ss3.png' , __FILE__ ) ?>" /></p><p>The close button will only work when used on the actual blog (frontend) and not in this example. Also note that the close button may give problems with earlier versions of Internet Explorer. It is also recommended that you have the latest version of jQuery on your blog (Version 1.7+ recommended).</p> </div></div><div id="sidebar"> <h3> Like This Plugin? </h3> <p> You can show your appreciation for this plugin by rating it on the Wordpress.org. </p></p><br/><h3> Have a question?</h3><p> Drop us a message at this <a href="http://www.techoot.com/contact"> Contact Form </a> with Notice Boxes as the subject. I will be happy to help you out.</p><br/></div></div>